// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - MM_Rogue_SL4-5_Task_01 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DialogTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2696988150" "Come...come on...{HeroName}...we can work this out. You have to...if you just KNEW why I needed that weapon...you'd see...that <i>I'm</i> the one who should have it...not whoever...you're going to sell it to...!"
// Answer Text :
"P2159026113" "Everyone has a story Frostfire - not everyone has money for it."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P2410886640" "Just...listen...I get that weapon into Longbow's hands...they'll see...they'll see that I can change.<br><br>And I <i>want</i> to change...I'm sick and tired of being...of the way they all look at me! Of who I've become!"
// Answer Text :
"P1516281438" "Save the sob story, Frostfire. You want this instead? Pay up."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P3482866060" "I don't have that kind of money! Come on...can't you just help out...someone for once?"
// Answer Text :
"P3549929374" "That's not what I do Frostfire. Now beat it, I'm not sticking around."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P3004551630" "<color orange>Frostfire regains his composure and lunges to attack you!"
// Answer Text :
"P998804733" "Of course...!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - KeyMissing 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P1692053110" "Missing Key"
// DetailString :
"P2443180657" "You looked through the supposed location of the key to the safe only to find it missing!<br><br>You found only ragged claw marks along where the key should been - telltale signs of the villain Mangle.<br><br>He's probably on his way now to getting that gun for himself!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - SafeKey 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2813787027" "Safe Key"
// DetailString :
"P2367284689" "Upon his defeat, Mangle teleported away, dropping the key to the safe nearby. He let out these final words as he was whisked away...<br><br><color CadetBlue>No one could understand - not you, not the others in the Isles, or those do-gooders in Paragon. No one could understand the task in front of me - and no one can stop me. We'll meet again one day, {HeroName}, and on that day you will wish you had never crossed me!</color>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - SafeOpen 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P3673658625" "The Dimensional Raygun"
// DetailString :
"P3624357531" "You pull out this strange device from the safe - it's somewhat heavy, with a large tank attached to the top part of the rifle. This has to be the dimensional raygun that everyone is after!<br><br>Moments after retreiving the device, an alarm goes off within the safe, followed by the sound of someone speaking on a radio - from within the safe!<br><br><color CadetBlue>I assumed you'd be here, {HeroName}. My name is Hollow Point, and I'm here to ensure <i>no one</i> gets this weapon. I could have simply destroyed it myself...but I figured it would lure someone like you along - two birds with one stone, you see.<br><br>I'd sit tight if I were you - I've called in some...friends from Wyvern to bomb this place in moments. Enjoy your last moments!</color><br><br>Judging by the radio, Hollow Point must be somewhere nearby - most likely around the Sky Raider base, waiting to be lifted out before the bombing!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - Point 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P3227221108" "Hollow Point's Justice"
// DetailString :
"P382609328" "Hollow Point's medi-porter whisked him away, though he dropped a document detailing the plan of this operation - just like he said. Wyvern will be here shortly to bomb carpet bomb this entire place - with you in it! <br><br>It also seems the Sky Raider base has a secret - a small nuclear device! It's unclear what they planned to do with it but this document shows that the base is carrying it.<br><br>Even if you were to get out of here, you would still be caught in the nuclear blast when Wyvern's bombing run comes through!<br><br>However...Longbow has been known to keep Wyvern in their place. To keep yourself out of this mess, you could radio in Longbow, showing them Wyvern's plan - it will no doubt cause them to send in their own men to intercept Wyvern - allowing you to slip out in the process!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P1102803381" "This plan of Frostfire's doesn't seem that hare-brained after all. Even though it sounds like he wants to go back to Paragon City - that's his own problem. You, however, want a bigger slice of the pie, and this is a wonderful opportunity.<br><br>You find out this weapon is called a <color yellow>Dimensional Raygun</color> - a prototype of a weapon in the works. Supposedly if you fire a bullet from this gun, it will shoot out from the barrel and teleport to the exact same spot in another dimension, continuing its course. It would theoretically allow a person to shoot someone else in another dimension.<br><br>There are a lot of buyers out there for this - Longbow is up there, but above them is a man named James S. Thompson.<br><br>Currently the Sky Raiders and Council are fighting over possession of the weapon - with Frostfire trying to outsmart them both. If you can stow away one in of the boats that head out towards the Sky Raider's ocean platform, you can likely sneak in past all the ruckus going on between and grab the parts you need.<br><br><color orange>WARNING: This is a Morality Mission. Completing this mission will change your alignment to Rogue. This means that the people of Paragon City and the Rogue Isle will no longer see you as a Villain. Becoming a Rogue means you will be able to move between Paragon City and the Rogue Isles.</color>"
// AcceptString :
"P2733922069" "Stow away on a ship going to the Sky Raider platform!"
// SendOffString :
"P3608283759" "You make plans to get onto a boat going for the Sky Raider platform - all that's left is to rendezvous with the boat and make your move once you arrive!"
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3926575342" "Steal the Dimensional Raygun!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3897494061" "You'll have to prepare yourself, as you'll be walking into a large firefight once you get out of that cargo ship."
// TaskTitle :
"P1084871662" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Frostfire's Foiled Gambit</color></span></scale></font>"
// TaskSubTitle :
"P292316059" "<span align=center><color orange><i>Rogue Morality Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P3415390569" "The boat stops, only to have a horde of Sky Raiders invade it. It turns out you were on the boat carrying the gun - only it's locked in a secured safe. And the Sky Raiders have the sole key to that safe!<br><br>You'll have to get that key to get the gun and your payday!"
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P1618882953" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Frostfire's Foiled Gambit</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color red><i>Morality Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You return safely from the Sky Raider platform, having obtained the Dimensional Raygun and stopped a small nuclear explosion from going off.<br><br>You contact James S. Thompson, who sends one of his representatives to pick up the gun and deliver your money - you notice that he has paid you extra, with a note that's attached to the wad of cash...<br><br><color CadetBlue>Thank you for your work, {HeroName}. Take this extra cash as my...appreciation for keeping this operation between the two of us.</color>"

